						<div class="postbody">Now that the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_sprite_evaluation" class="postlink">PPU's actual sprite processing behavior</a> is better understood, here's the revised advice: You have to turn off rendering between x=128 + 6 * (number of sprites in range) and x=256. Get it as close as you can to the right side [TPIR]without going over[/TPIR] and you should be fine.</div>

